com.delphix.masking.api.plugin

Interface PluginComponent

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    DiscoveryClassifier, MaskingAlgorithm<T>, MaskingComponent

    public interface PluginComponent
    This is the interface that all classes that wish to expose functionality to the Delphix Masking engine must implement. The type of component implemented by a class is determined by which usage-specific interface is implemented by the class - for example, MaskingAlgorithm if the component is a masking algorithm.

    The usage-specific (DriverSupport, for example) interface will also define how instances of that type will be configured, by adding either JsonConfigurable or PropertyConfigurable to the set of interfaces implemented, or no configuration interface in the plugin component instances don't support configuration. The interface MaskingAlgorithm is a special case, implementing the MaskingComponent, which adds additional concepts around default instances.

    Licence, author, version and other information may be included directly or by reference in the getDocumentation() markup. These items should also be included in the metadata of the plugin JAR that provides the component.
